First create the following directory structure in your home directory.
mkdir -p ~/.vim ~/.vim/autoload ~/.vim/backup ~/.vim/colors ~/.vim/plugged

Create a .vimrc file in your home directory by 
touch ~/.vimrc

now copy and paste the lines from master file. 
save the file and close. 

To install the vim-plug plugin, run this command:
$ curl -fLo ~/.vim/autoload/plug.vim --create-dirs \
    https://raw.githubusercontent.com/junegunn/vim-plug/master/plug.vim

Now type :PlugInstall to download and install the two plugins.

keybindings
zo to open a single fold under the cursor.
zc to close the fold under the cursor.
zR to open all folds.
zM to close all folds.

vimtex keybindings:
\ll to start/stop the compiling 
\lk to stop the compiling 
\lc to clear auxilary files 

referrence
https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/vimrc-configuration-guide-customize-your-vim-editor/
https://github.com/lervag/vimtex
